Iatrogenic epidermoid cyst of the parotid region following ear surgery.
 Iatrogenic implantation of squamous epithelium may result in formation of an epidermoid cyst.
 These cysts have been described in various sites around the head and neck following otological procedures.
 A case of iatrogenic epidermal cyst in the parotid region following repeated myringoplasty is reported.
 The clinical features and differential diagnosis are discussed.
